Love this pattern. Here’s a clean, reusable production blueprint for “knowledge-asset + intelligent backend + insight UI” (your Vriddhi case: stock database + optimizer + web app). It’s generic enough to reuse for other domains later.

1) High-level architecture (3 layers)
Knowledge Asset Layer (KA): your proprietary datasets (e.g., stocks table + derived factors, forecasts). Versioned, access-controlled, and auditable.

Intelligence Layer (IL): services that read the KA and produce decisions/insights (e.g., stock selector, optimizer, risk checks).

Experience Layer (XL): UI that collects user intents, calls IL APIs, and renders insights (charts, tables, narratives).

2) Core components
Data store (KA): Postgres (OLTP) + object storage (CSV/Parquet snapshots) for versioning; optional Redis cache for hot reads.

Service API (IL): FastAPI (Python) with endpoints like /optimize, /universe, /backtest.

Batch/Async (IL): Celery/RQ + worker for heavy runs; scheduled jobs for nightly factor refresh.

Secrets & Config: GCP Secret Manager (or AWS SSM), env-per-stage (dev, staging, prod).

UI (XL): React/Next.js (or Streamlit v1 for speed), calls IL via HTTPS.

CI/CD: GitHub Actions → build, test, image, deploy to Cloud Run (or ECS).

Observability: structured logs, OpenTelemetry traces, Prometheus metrics, uptime checks.

Security: VPC, private DB, least-privileged service accounts, row-level ACLs if multi-tenant, e2e TLS, signed JWTs.

3) Data model (minimal, extensible)
Postgres (KA)

stocks(id, ticker, name, sector, currency, active, created_at, data_version)

fundamentals(stock_id, asof_date, metric, value, data_version)

forecasts(stock_id, asof_date, exp_return, exp_vol, exp_div_yield, model_tag, data_version)

constraints(asof_date, key, value, scope) // e.g., max weight per stock/sector

runs(run_id, user_id, asof_date, params_json, code_version, data_version, started_at, finished_at, status)

allocations(run_id, stock_id, weight, rationale, diagnostics_json)

Why: every portfolio is reproducible (pin code_version + data_version + params_json). This protects IP and enables audits.

4) Service contracts (IL)
POST /optimize

Input (JSON):

