}
Output:

{
  "run_id": "RUN-20250815-123456",
  "summary": {"exp_cagr":0.185,"stdev":0.19,"drawdown":0.28},
  "allocations": [{"ticker":"INFY","weight":0.10,"explain":"quality+earnings"},
                  {"ticker":"HDFCBANK","weight":0.12,"explain":"valuation+moat"}],
  "constraints_applied": {...},
  "data_version": "KA-2025-08-15T00:05Z",
  "code_version": "vriddhi-il@a1b2c3d",
  "diagnostics": {"solver":"OSQP","iterations":231}
}
GET /runs/{run_id} → status & results (supports async workers).
GET /universe?asof_date=...&tag=core20 → what the optimizer can pick from.

5) Protecting the knowledge asset (KA)
Network: Private DB (no public IP), IL runs inside VPC; only IL can read/write KA; UI never touches DB directly.

AuthZ: Service account with read-only to forecasts & fundamentals, write-only to runs/allocations.

Encryption: At rest (DB + object store) and in transit (TLS). Column-level encryption for sensitive vendor data if any.

Versioning: Immutable Parquet snapshots in object storage with manifest (e.g., data_version hash). Only IL chooses which version to serve.

IP controls: Rate limits, signed requests (JWT), WAF, and request logging with PII minimization.

6) Caching & performance
Hot cache (Redis): cache /universe and common /optimize results keyed by (params_hash, data_version).

Result reuse: if same user repeats identical params against same data version, return cached run_id.

Async runs: long optimizations → enqueue job, return run_id immediately, UI polls /runs/{id}.

7) Deployment topology (fast path)
GCP Cloud Run

vriddhi-il (FastAPI) container, autoscaled, private.

vriddhi-ui (Next.js) public.

vriddhi-worker (Celery) on Cloud Run Jobs or Cloud Run service with min=1.

Postgres via Cloud SQL (private IP).

Secrets: Secret Manager.

Object store: GCS for snapshots/artifacts.

CI/CD: GitHub Actions → build images → Artifact Registry → deploy.

